---
/** StatsGrid — Figma node 8:30 */
---

<section class="bg-navy py-20 sm:py-28 lg:py-32">
  <div class="max-w-[1232px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <!-- Section label -->
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-white/60 mb-4">What you actually get</p>
    <div class="w-12 h-0.5 bg-accent mb-12 sm:mb-16"></div>

    <!-- 2-col grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-20">
      <!-- Left: heading -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading font-medium text-white text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl leading-tight">
          Kit that works. One number when it doesn't.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: stat rows -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
        <!-- Stat 1 -->
        <div class="border-b border-accent pb-8">
          <h3 class="font-heading font-medium text-white text-lg mb-2">Set up properly from day one</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm mb-4">
            Till, card machine, bookings and broadband chosen to work together, so nothing clashes and nothing dies halfway through service.
          </p>
          <p class="font-heading font-medium text-accent text-5xl sm:text-6xl">1 setup</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Stat 2 -->
        <div class="border-b border-accent pb-8">
          <h3 class="font-heading font-medium text-white text-lg mb-2">One number. No call centre.</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm mb-4">
            When something goes down, you ring me. Not a ticket queue, and not someone who'll blame the other provider. Just me, and I'll sort it.
          </p>
          <p class="font-heading font-medium text-accent text-5xl sm:text-6xl">1 call</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Stat 3 -->
        <div class="border-b border-accent pb-8">
          <h3 class="font-heading font-medium text-white text-lg mb-2">One venue or thirty</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm mb-4">
            Works the same way whether you're running a pub on your own or a group of sites. Same number, same bloke on the end of it.
          </p>
          <p class="font-heading font-medium text-accent text-5xl sm:text-6xl">1&ndash;30+</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
